          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>1 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: E 16269 B; Qurʾānic Text: Q 2:226-2:228; 7 lines per page; Dimensions: 100 x 128mm; Estimated date of production: 750-900 (?). </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue of Arabic manuscripts kept by the University Museum in Philaldelphia, written by Giorgio Levi Della Vida gives the following information (<ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/78QP9SWH">Levi Della Vida 1981</ref>, p. 161f.):</p>
              <p>"132.  Inv. E. 16269 B. 3rd-4th century A.H./9th-10th century A.D. Yellowish,  thin parchment 12.8 x 10 cm. Full size page from a very small copy. The  upper left corner and the lower side are damaged. The margins are  partially preserved (upper: 1.5 cm. lower: 2.1 cm. outer: 1.7 cm. inner:  1.5 cm.). Written on both faces, seven lines to the page, in black ink.  From the Ellen W. Harrison Collection. <hi rend="italic">Recto</hi>: رجيم [sic!] – 228 خلق. Verso: 2,228 ارحامهن – اصلاحًا و(لهن). The script is rather angular "Kūfic", presenting a mixture of older and younger features. Some <hi rend="italic">alifs</hi> bend to the right with their lower ends, some do not. The shaft of the <hi rend="italic">ṭāʾ </hi>is curved on recto line 2 (in الطلق verse 227) and straight on recto line 4 (in والمطلقات, verse 228). Final <hi rend="italic">yāʾ </hi>is reversed, final <hi rend="italic">qāf</hi> is doubly curved. Diacritical signs are expressed by short and thick strokes, which in the letter <hi rend="italic">thāʾ</hi> are placed one above the other. Vowels are marked in red: <hi rend="italic">hamz </hi>and <hi rend="italic">tashdīd</hi>  are not marked. A golden pear-shaped verse divider appears after verse  227 (on recto line 8), which is 225 according to the Damascus, Mecca and  Medina numbering (see <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/PWGCAS53">A. Spitaler, <hi rend="italic">Die Verszählung des Koran</hi></ref>, p.33)." </p>
            </summary>
